main event: An unidentified flying object was sighted over the Hawaiian Islands on March 11, 1963.
interesting points: The object was first thought to be a jet at high altitude but was later confirmed to be moving at a higher speed than any known aircraft,It left a vapor trail during its flight over the islands,Residents and tourists were engaged in the event, with numerous reports flooding local newspapers and radio stations,Two National Guard pilots reported visual contact with the object which appeared crescent-shaped and very bright.
witness description: Residents, tourists, and National Guard pilots
